Which of the following practices can cause a test tube to crack?
① Heating the test tube with the outer flame of an alcohol burner;
② Not drying the outer wall of the test tube before heating;
③ Letting the bottom of the test tube touch the wick during heating;
④ Heating the test tube with liquid exceeding 1/3 of its capacity;
⑤ Heating a single area on the test tube containing liquid without preheating.
